b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe48243.htm)  [Next](sbe48245.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n41\\. And there is not (origination) of the instrument from the agent.\n\n'The internal organ called Pradyumna originates from Sa _n_ karsha _n_ a,' i.\ne. the internal organ originates from the individual soul which is the agent.\nBut this is inadmissible, since the text 'from him there is produced breath,\nmind, and all sense-organs' (Mu. Up. II, 1, 3) declares that the mind also\nsprings from none else but the highest Brahman. As the Bhagavata doctrine thus\nteaches things opposed to Scripture, its authoritativeness cannot be admitted.\n--Against these objections the next Sutra declares itself.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: 42. Or, if they are of the nature of that which is\nknowledge...](sbe48245.htm)\n\n"